javax.time.calendrical

Interface PeriodUnit.PeriodBetween

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DateTime.MinusAdjuster, DateTime.PlusAdjuster
    Enclosing interface:
    PeriodUnit

    public static interface PeriodUnit.PeriodBetween
extends DateTime.PlusAdjuster, DateTime.MinusAdjuster
    Simple period representing the amount of time between two date-time objects.

    This interface is the return type from PeriodUnit.between(R, R). It represents an amount of time measured in a single unit. It can be queried for the amount and unit, or added directly to another date-time: 

      date = date.minus(MONTHS.between(start, end));

    Implementation notes

    This interface must be implemented with care to ensure other classes operate correctly. All implementations that can be instantiated must be final, immutable and thread-safe.
